profile_positions.description:
‣ Assisted the Sustainability Lead in planning and organising projects in the university: SDG education, procurement and travel policy, sustainable events, waste, decarbonisation, planet-proof canteen;
‣ Prepared and delivered presentations to university stakeholders, lobbying for sustainability changes;
‣ Helped evaluating and reviewing the Sustainable VU Strategy 2025 and suggested improvement points;
‣ Enhanced communication and reporting about sustainability initiatives within the VU community, by  producing written project proposals, minutes, handbooks, case studies etc.
‣ Assisted team members with desk research on a diverse range of sustainability themes (education, operations, knowledge transfer), depending on project needs.

‣ Executing credit audit reports to be presented to potential investors and banks, from Romania and abroad.
‣ Conducting monthly financial analysis and forecast for several SMEs and larger enterprises with a turnover over 15M euros;
‣ Determining client's eligibility for funding;
‣ Periodically running market research in agriculture, pharma and distribution fields.

• Worked within the Europe Direct Information Centre (EDIC) that aims to promote the values of the European Union to all citizens;
• Promoted participatory citizenship through different communication tools (website, social media, publications, monthly newsletter etc.);
• Provided information, advice, assistance and answers to questions about the EU, in particular regarding EU citizens' rights, EU priorities, its legislation, policies, programs and funding opportunities.

volunteer_experiences.description:
• Participated in over 15 national and international debate forums (Romania, Serbia, Spain, Czech Republic, Belgium);
• Involved in the simulation of the EP committees from the perspective of a delegate, chairperson and, later on, president;
• Starting with 2019, I coordinated the Training & Academics Department whose role is to create the debate topics, ensure the academic preparation of all 9 annual events and train the future generations of EYPers;
• European-recognised certificate in training and facilitation of learning due to participation in the Erasmus+ funded programme "European Youth Training - Shaping a Network through Training" in March 2019;
• Prepared and delivered extensive training modules;
• Authored guidelines and EYP-related documents to help the transfer of tacit knowledge to other members;
• Acquired flexibility and confidence as well as global knowledge, critical thinking and the ability to express ideas through moderated discussion on a broad range of current topics.

ISN Amsterdam is a student-run non-profit organization dedicated to helping international students studying at the Universiteit van Amsterdam (UvA) and Hogeschool van Amsterdam (HvA) make the most of their stay in the Netherlands.

• Organised with the committee over 15 university-funded events aimed at promoting intercultural understanding between 1k+ international students;
• Logistical preparation and in-person conduct;
• Contacted small Dutch businesses to establish partnership agreements in order to fit our events in the planned budget.

• Actively involved in the International Affairs community at training sessions on foreign policy and international relations; 
• Organised the 30+ participants educational project named Worldwide Institutions Academy, managing its Digital Marketing and HR strategy; 
• Sourced valuable speakers for panels on the global economic mechanisms behind World Bank and WTO.

• Formed a solid knowledge base of governmental actions and global issues;
• Learnt how to apply the procedure and conduct effectively a MUN debate;
• Enhanced diplomacy and negotiation skills;
• Coordinated the Chairpersons Team and the efficient transition to the next Executive Board;
• Established long-term and short-term goals including fundraisers, recruitment campaigns and promotion events;
• Developed leadership skills and exercised methods of research, public speaking, and teamwork.
